 shipment would include movie-based information where the user could only view the content. In the second phase, we decided to include user interactions and personalization. </p> <div class=\"d-flex py-3\"> <div class=\"d-flex flex-fill flex-column\"> <div class=\"d-flex\"> <span class=\"sub-heading highlight-orange p-2\"> Essential </span> </div> <div class=\"d-flex py-2 flex-column\"> <img src=\"83d625f34a8513cc2d8c20826f35ba5c.svg\" class=\"svg-icon my-2\" alt=\"\"> <span class=\"d-flex secondary-heading color-white pb-1\"> Relevance </span> <p class=\"paragraph\"> How might we present relevant movies initially from 10,000+ movies with minimal user effort. </p> </div> <div class=\"d-flex py-2 flex-column\"> <img src=\"83d625f34a8513cc2d8c20826f35ba5c.svg\" class=\"svg-icon my-2\" alt=\"\"> <span class=\"d-flex secondary-heading color-white pb-1\"> Relevance </span> <p class=\"paragraph\"> How might be ensure every movie is easily discoverable and grouped in a more contextual way. </p> </div> <div class=\"d-flex py-2 flex-column\"> <img src=\"83d625f34a8513cc2d8c20826f35ba5c.svg\" class=\"svg-icon my-2\" alt=\"\"> <span class=\"d-flex secondary-heading color-white pb-1\"> Informative </span> <p class=\"paragraph\"> How might we prioritize each piece of information about movie, cast & crew and present it to the user without cognitive overloading. </p> </div> </div> <div class=\"d-flex flex-fill flex-column\"> <div class=\"d-flex\"> <span class=\"sub-heading highlight-orange p-2\"> Necessary </span> </div> <div class=\"d-flex py-2 flex-column\"> <img src=\"83d625f34a8513cc2d8c20826f35ba5c.svg\" class=\"svg-icon my-2\" alt=\"\"> <span class=\"d-flex secondary-heading color-white pb-1\"> Preference </span> <p class=\"paragraph\"> How might we provide personalization to the users and ensure that their preference is emphasized. </p> </div> <div class=\"d-flex py-2 flex-column\"> <img src=\"83d625f34a8513cc2d8c20826f35ba5c.svg\" class=\"svg-icon my-2\" alt=\"\"> <span class=\"d-flex secondary-heading color-white pb-1\"> Efficiency </span> <p class=\"paragraph\"> How might be provide customization and quickness during the discoverability phase. </p> </div> <div class=\"d-flex py-2 flex-column\"> <img src=\"83d625f34a8513cc2d8c20826f35ba5c.svg\" class=\"svg-icon my-2\" alt=\"\"> <span class=\"d-flex secondary-heading color-white pb-1\"> Engagement </span> <p class=\"paragraph\"> How might be incorporate user actions from the existing website to the mobile app and improvize the user engagement experience </p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"d-flex flex-fill pb-5\"> <div class=\"d-flex pt-3\"> <span class=\"d-flex rectangle\"> </span> <span class=\"sub-heading pl-3 color-white\">FEB 2018</span> </div> <div class=\"d-flex flex-column\"> <div class=\"d-flex\"> <div class=\"d-flex flex-column flex-fill px-3\"> <span class=\"sub-heading py-2\">Identifying</span> <div class=\"d-flex heading pb-4\"> <span class=\"pr-3\">The</span> <span class=\"highlight-orange px-1\">Essentials</span> </div> <span class=\"sub-heading color-white py-3\"> Location Selection </span> <p class=\"paragraph pb-4\"> To provide relevant information, we allowed the user to detect or choose their location to filter out the movies release patterns and showtime availability in their location </p> <span class=\"sub-heading color-white py-3\"> Movie Release Timeline and Search </span> <p class=\"paragraph pb-4\"> To provide better discoverability, we arranged the information based on release date in a timeline fashion along with language filter and search options </p> </div> <img src=\"11ce9f7cd82a3b3e0627dbee1e4b150e.jpg\" height=\"700\" width=\"320\" class=\"mx-5 image-full-width-small\" alt=\"\"> </div> <div class=\"d-flex flex-fill pb-5\"> <img src=\"11ce9f7cd82a3b3e0627dbee1e4b150e.jpg\" height=\"700\" width=\"320\" class=\"mx-5 image-full-width-small\" alt=\"\"> <div class=\"d-flex pt-5 flex-column flex-fill px-3\"> <span class=\"sub-heading color-white py-3\"> Movie Information </span> <p class=\"paragraph pb-4\"> Based on the information architecture, we prioritized the information of the movie page. We rearranged the information based on the life cycle of the movie which is from the announcement of the movie to the archival of it. </p> <span class=\"sub-heading color-white py-3\"> What’s New Section </span> <p class=\"paragraph pb-4\"> This section in the movie page provides information that are latest and automatically gets updated based on the information getting added to the page. </p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"d-flex flex-fill pb-5\"> <div class=\"d-flex pt-3\"> <span class=\"d-flex rectangle\"> </span> <span class=\"sub-heading pl-3 color-white\">FEB 2018</span> </div> <div class=\"d-flex flex-column\"> <p class=\"secondary-heading color-white pb-4\"> “<span class=\"highlight-orange\">Before</span> moving to the <span class=\"highlight-orange\">necessary phase</span>, we identified few criticial issues such as components’ <span class=\"highlight-orange\">consistency</span> and <span class=\"highlight-orange\">accessibiltiy standards.</span>” </p> <div class=\"d-flex py-3\"> <div class=\"d-flex flex-column\"> <div class=\"d-flex p-3 border-left-active flex-column\"> <div class=\"d-flex align-items-center secondary-heading color-white\"> <span class=\"d-flex pt-1\"> Content Overflowing </span> <img src=\"83d625f34a8513cc2d8c20826f35ba5c.svg\" class=\"svg-icon\" alt=\"\"> </div> <p class=\"paragraph py-2\"> Overflowing information for larger dispaly text size is mainly in ios resulting in lose of content </p> </div> <div class=\"d-flex p-3 border-left flex-column\"> <div class=\"d-flex align-items-center secondary-heading color-white\"> <span class=\"d-flex pt-1\"> Content Overflowing </span> <img src=\"83d625f34a8513cc2d8c20826f35ba5c.svg\" class=\"svg-icon\" alt=\"\"> </div> <p class=\"paragraph py-2\"> Overflowing information for larger dispaly text size is mainly in ios resulting in lose of content </p> </div> <div class=\"d-flex p-3 border-left flex-column\"> <div class=\"d-flex align-items-center secondary-heading color-white\"> <span class=\"d-flex pt-1\"> Content Overflowing </span> <img src=\"83d625f34a8513cc2d8c20826f35ba5c.svg\" class=\"svg-icon\" alt=\"\"> </div> <p class=\"paragraph py-2\"> Overflowing information for larger dispaly text size is mainly in ios resulting in lose of content </p> </div> </div> <img src=\"11ce9f7cd82a3b3e0627dbee1e4b150e.jpg\" height=\"700\" width=\"320\" class=\"mx-5 image-full-width-small\" alt=\"\"> </div> <p class=\"secondary-heading color-white py-4\"> So we came up with a <span class=\"highlight-orange\">sustainable design system</span> and relooked at the overall experience to address the above issues </p> </div> </div> <div class=\"d-flex flex-fill pb-5\"> <div class=\"d-flex pt-3\"> <span class=\"d-flex rectangle\"> </span> <span class=\"sub-heading pl-3 color-white\">FEB 2018</span> </div> <div class=\"d-flex flex-column\"> <span class=\"sub-heading py-2\">Defining</span> <div class=\"d-flex heading pb-4\"> <span class=\"pr-3\">The</span> <span class=\"highlight-orange px-1\">Design System</span> </div> <p class=\"paragraph py-3\"> We listed out the principles in such a way that our design system should provide a fluid and hassle free experience to all the user segments of our product. Few of the key principles are as follows: </p> <div class=\"d-flex flex-fill pb-4\"> <div class=\"card p-3 m-2 flex-fill flex-row d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center paragraph tag text-with-highlight\"> <img src=\"10571d2bd3e16fedce1b168f5d56edf9.svg\" class=\"svg-icon\" alt=\"\"> <span class=\"d-flex py-3 px-2 highlights\">Adaptability</span> </div> <div class=\"card p-3 m-2 flex-fill flex-row d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center paragraph tag text-with-highlight\"> <img src=\"10571d2bd3e16fedce1b168f5d56edf9.svg\" class=\"svg-icon\" alt=\"\"> <span class=\"d-flex py-3 px-2 highlights\">